Updates `esbuild` from 0.25.6 to 0.25.8
Release notes

Sourced from esbuild's releases.

v0.25.8

  • Fix another TypeScript parsing edge case (#4248)

    This fixes a regression with a change in the previous release that tries to more accurately parse TypeScript arrow functions inside the ?: operator. The regression specifically involves parsing an arrow function containing a #private identifier inside the middle of a ?: ternary operator inside a class body. This was fixed by propagating private identifier state into the parser clone used to speculatively parse the arrow function body. Here is an example of some affected code:

    class CachedDict {
  #has = (a: string) => dict.has(a);
  has = window
    ? (word: string): boolean => this.#has(word)
    : this.#has;
}

  • Fix a regression with the parsing of source phase imports

    The change in the previous release to parse source phase imports failed to properly handle the following cases:

    import source from 'bar'
import source from from 'bar'
import source type foo from 'bar'

    Parsing for these cases should now be fixed. The first case was incorrectly treated as a syntax error because esbuild was expecting the second case. And the last case was previously allowed but is now forbidden. TypeScript hasn't added this feature yet so it remains to be seen whether the last case will be allowed, but it's safer to disallow it for now. At least Babel doesn't allow the last case when parsing TypeScript, and Babel was involved with the source phase import specification.

v0.25.7

  • Parse and print JavaScript imports with an explicit phase (#4238)

    This release adds basic syntax support for the defer and source import phases in JavaScript:

    • defer

      This is a stage 3 proposal for an upcoming JavaScript feature that will provide one way to eagerly load but lazily initialize imported modules. The imported module is automatically initialized on first use. Support for this syntax will also be part of the upcoming release of TypeScript 5.9. The syntax looks like this:

      import defer * as foo from "<specifier>";
const bar = await import.defer("<specifier>");

      Note that this feature deliberately cannot be used with the syntax import defer foo from "<specifier>" or import defer { foo } from "<specifier>".

    • source

      This is a stage 3 proposal for an upcoming JavaScript feature that will provide another way to eagerly load but lazily initialize imported modules. The imported module is returned in an uninitialized state. Support for this syntax may or may not be a part of TypeScript 5.9 (see this issue for details). The syntax looks like this:

      import source foo from "<specifier>";
const bar = await import.source("<specifier>");

issue.title: 女娲角色创建时使用了错误的目录路径
issue.body:
## 问题描述

女娲角色在创建新角色时，错误地将角色文件放置在了`user/role/`目录下，而正确的路径应该是`resource/role/`。

## 问题细节

- **当前行为**：女娲使用filesystem工具创建角色时，路径为`user/role/{roleId}/`
- **期望行为**：应该创建在`resource/role/{roleId}/`
- **影响**：创建的角色无法被PromptX系统正确发现和加载

## 复现步骤

1. 激活女娲角色
2. 请求创建一个新角色（如Taylor）
3. 观察创建的文件路径
4. 发现角色被创建在`~/.promptx/user/role/`而不是`~/.promptx/resource/role/`

## 建议修复

更新女娲角色的execution文件，明确指定正确的角色创建路径为`resource/role/`

## 相关组件

- 女娲角色
- 角色创建功能
- 文件系统路径管理

Un instructor debe poder:

1. Crear una evaluación y asociarla a un curso y sección.
2. Agregar preguntas a la evaluacion.
3. Agregar opciones a las preguntas y definir cual es la respuesta correcta.
4. Publicar una evaluacion

1. Analizar los formularios existentes.
2. Analizar el esquema de la base de datos.
3. Analizar las rutas definidas.
4. Agregar plantillas existentes si faltan.
5. Agregar rutas pendientes si faltan.

Un estudiente debe:

1. Poder inscribirse a un curso
2. Marcar los recursos como completados.
3. Ver las pruebas disponibles
4. Intentar responderlas
5. Obtener un certificado de finalización si completa todos recursos y las evaluaciones requeridas.

Cuando el sistema se inicializa se crea un archivo de prueba llamada "now" en now_lms/db/initial_data.py

El curso deberia contar una evaluación muy basica de ejemplo relacionado con la educación en linea para demostrar a usuarios que estan probando el sistema por primera vez como funciona el sistema de evaluaciones.

Esta funcionalidad es critica para el sistema y se debe probar rigurosamente tanto con propuebas unitatias como  con pruevas end to end.

Hacegurar que todas las pruebas pasen al finalizar la implementación.

pull_request.title: Complete evaluation functionality with example evaluation in "now" course
pull_request.body:
This PR implements the missing pieces to ensure the evaluation functionality is complete and provides a working example for new users.

## Problem
The issue identified that while the evaluation system had most components implemented (database models, forms, routes, templates), it was missing:
1. A basic evaluation example in the "now" course to demonstrate the system to first-time users
2. A critical missing route (`edit_question`) that was causing 500 errors when trying to edit evaluations

## Solution

### Added Example Evaluation to "now" Course
Created a comprehensive example evaluation called "Online Teaching Knowledge Check" that gets automatically created when the system initializes:

- **3 diverse questions** covering online education fundamentals in Spanish
- **Mixed question types**: multiple choice and boolean questions  
- **Proper configuration**: 70% passing score, 3 maximum attempts
- **Complete options setup**: Each question has all options configured with correct answers marked

The evaluation is created by a new `crear_evaluacion_predeterminada()` function integrated into the application initialization sequence.

### Fixed Missing Route
Added the missing `edit_question` route and template that was referenced in the evaluation edit interface but not implemented:

- **New route**: `/instructor/questions/<question_id>/edit`
- **Complete template**: `edit_question.html` with full editing interface
- **Proper permissions**: Checks instructor ownership and admin override
- **Error handling**: Graceful handling of missing questions/evaluations

### Technical Implementation
```python
# Example of the evaluation creation
evaluacion = Evaluation(
    section_id=seccion.id,
    title="Online Teaching Knowledge Check", 
    description="A basic evaluation to test your understanding of online teaching fundamentals",
    is_exam=False,
    passing_score=70.0,
    max_attempts=3
)
```

The implementation follows the existing patterns and integrates seamlessly with the current codebase.

## Validation
- ✅ All 23 evaluation-related tests pass
- ✅ Manual testing confirms evaluation appears in instructor interface
- ✅ Student enrollment and evaluation access verified programmatically
- ✅ Code quality maintained (Black formatting, Flake8 linting)

This provides a complete, working evaluation system that demonstrates all key functionality to new NOW-LMS users while fixing the critical editing bug.

Fixes #71.

pull_request.title: Add Giscus comment system positioned after tags section on blog posts
pull_request.body:
This PR implements a Giscus-powered comment system for individual blog posts on the Docusaurus site. Comments appear directly after the tags section (not at the bottom of the page) with a consistent light theme and production-ready configuration.

## What's Added

- **@giscus/react integration**: Added the official Giscus React component package
- **SSR-safe GiscusComments component**: A wrapper component that handles server-side rendering compatibility 
- **BlogPostItem enhancement**: Swizzled the BlogPostItem component to include comments positioned after the tags section on individual post pages
- **Production configuration**: Configured with the correct repository ID, category, and GitHub Discussions settings

## Technical Implementation

The implementation uses Docusaurus's component swizzling feature to wrap the existing BlogPostItem component. Comments are conditionally rendered based on URL pattern matching (`/YYYY/MM/DD/post-name`) and blog post page detection to ensure they only appear on individual blog posts.

The component architecture prevents SSR issues by separating the hook usage into a browser-only internal component:
- `GiscusCommentsInternal` contains the Giscus React component with fixed light theme
- `GiscusComments` wraps it with Docusaurus's `BrowserOnly` component

## Configuration

The comment system uses production-ready settings:
- Repository: `davidelettieri/davidelettieri.it`
- Repository ID: `MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnkxMDMwNTcwMDM=`
- Category: Announcements  
- Category ID: `DIC_kwDOBiSGa84CuIrP`
- Theme: Light (fixed, no dynamic switching)
- Input position: Top
- Mapping: pathname-based

## Key Features

- **Optimal positioning**: Comments appear immediately after the tags section for better content flow
- **SSR-compatible**: Uses proper component separation to prevent server-side rendering errors
- **Performance optimized**: Lazy loading and pathname-based comment mapping  
- **Consistent theming**: Fixed light theme for all users
- **User-friendly**: Comments integrate seamlessly with existing blog post layout
- **Accessible**: Maintains existing site navigation and styling

commits.message:
SherLoCK Version 0.02

# SherloCK — CHANGELOG

All notable changes to this project are documented here.

---

## [0.02] — 2025-08-17

### Added
- **Framed UI** with boxed sections, headings, and underlines across all tabs.
- **Header** now shows: Date/Time, **Uptime**, Mesh health gauge, and **Node bubbles** (● online / ○ offline).
- **Scrolling ticker** at bottom:
  - Loads plain-text messages from `banners/*.txt`.
  - Time/condition based items via `banners/schedule.json` (e.g., morning tips, heat alerts).
  - Runtime controls: `ticker color <green|cyan|yellow|magenta|white|red>`, `ticker speed <float>`, `ticker brightness <0|1|2>`, `ticker reload`.
- **Numeric device selection** on Scan: type index digits then **Enter** to open **Profile**.
- **AI tab sub-tabs** `[1..5]`: Overview, Patterns, Clusters, Focus, Tools (press number keys to switch).
- **BLE frame capture**:
  - Service **UUID set** history + per-device **top UUIDs**.
  - **Manufacturer data** (CID/len/sample) and **Service Data** (UUID16/sample) summaries.
- **Triangulation (skeleton usable today)**:
  - Anchors persisted in `config/anchors.json`.
  - Commands:
    - `tri set <NODE> <x> <y>` · `tri list` · `tri del <NODE>`
    - `tri watch add|del|list <mac>` — publish live RSSI to peers
    - `tri solve <mac> n1:x,y:-65 n2:... n3:...` (least-squares lateration)
    - `tri meshsolve <mac>` — aggregate anchors + RSSI from mesh peers
- **Mesh heartbeat** now includes `anchor` and `watch_rssi` for triangulation.
- **Shared learning**:
  - Mesh `training/` sync: publish local training CSV snapshot and **auto-merge** peer snapshots.
- **First-run bootstrap**:
  - Auto-creates `data/`, `config/`, `logs/`, `banners/`, default CSVs/JSON, a welcome banner, and a sample schedule.
- **System/cluster controls** (script commands):
  - `compute ai_workers <n>`
  - `compute threads <n>` (sets `OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS` / `OMP_NUM_THREADS`)
  - `compute governor <performance|powersave|schedutil>`
  - `compute affinity <cpu-list/ranges>` (e.g., `0-3,5`)
- **Settings tab** shows cores, load averages, RAM usage, sensor temperatures, total cumulative usage.
- **Session timer & usage persistence**:
  - `timer show` / `timer reset`
  - Cumulative usage saved to `config/usage.json`.

### Changed
- **Threat pattern display** is grouped (Identity/Dynamics/Correlation/Policy) to avoid long single lines.
- **AI investigation**: refined unstable RSSI, mirrored follower detection, name/UUID flap, co-appearance.
- **Tabs** moved into a dedicated box; key legend offloaded to the **ticker** to prevent overflow.
- **Profile** view expanded with UUID/mfr/service data sections and improved RSSI stats/sparkline.
- **Mesh Manager**: stronger health checks, atomic writes, training snapshot publish/merge helpers.

### Fixed
- UI dialog **indentation/syntax** problems (`draw_script_dialog`, `draw_ai_command_prompt`).
- **Threat rating** function docstring/indentation errors.
- **Key legend overflow** (e.g., `M:mode` falling off screen) by moving to ticker.
- **Numeric selection** not working → implemented buffered digit entry with timeout + page sync.
- **First run** crashes due to missing files/dirs → bootstrap now creates everything.
- **BLE missing** crash → runs UI without scanner if `bleak` not available; shows notice instead.
- **Curses edge overflows** → `safe_addstr` width checks and truncation across UI.
- **Mesh training merge** now logged; saves after successful merge.
- Safer file I/O using **atomic temp-file replace** for JSON/CSV writes.

### Performance/Stability
- Reduced redraw/layout errors; periodic auto-save/merge in janitor.
- Lower risk of partial file writes; better exception handling.
- Optional CPU affinity and thread knobs to scale compute vs. heat.

### Removed/Deprecated
- N/A (no breaking removals this release).

### Known Issues
- RSSI-based lateration is environment-sensitive; multipath can degrade accuracy without calibration.
- Triangulation requires **≥3 anchors** with known coordinates; ensure synchronized `tri set` on all nodes.
- Temperature sensors vary by platform; some systems may only show partial readings.

### Upgrade Notes (0.01 → 0.02)
1. Replace your `sherlock_nexus.py` with v0.02.
2. On first run, verify bootstrap created:
   - `data/`, `config/`, `logs/`, `banners/`, `config/anchors.json`, `config/usage.json`,
     `threat_db.csv`, `training_db.csv`, `banners/schedule.json`, `banners/00-welcome.txt`.
3. Optional: set anchors and try triangulation:
   ```text
   tri set NODEA 0 0
   tri set NODEB 10 0
   tri set NODEC 0 8
   tri watch add <target-mac>         # on all nodes
   tri meshsolve <target-mac>
